The paper discusses the use of evolutionary algorithms for diversity optimization, which is a common topic in the field of neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of diversity optimization for obtaining a better understanding of possible solutions to a problem is also relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). The experimental investigations involve evolving diverse sets of images, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV).
